Exercise 1.3: Define a procedure that takes three numbers as arguments and returns the sum of the squares of the two larger numbers. 

---

(define (sum-larger-square x y z)
  (cond
    ((and (< x y) (< x z)) (+(* y y)(* z z)))
    ((and (< y z) (< y x)) (+(* z z)(* x x)))
    (else (+(* x x)(* y y)))))
